<div style="max-width:75%; text-align:center; margin-left:auto; margin-right:auto;" class="d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-content-center text-start">
    <h1 class="p-4 my-5 custom-title" style="font-size: 80px; font-weight: 700;">Sessions</h1>
    <h4 class="text-center mt-4 mb-5">Sessions are the way to store and retrieve user data on the server side between different requests.</h4>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">
        You can use sessions to store user-specific information such as login credentials, shopping cart contents, and more.
        when you store data in session. it will not be deleted until you deleted through clearing the session from browser or code logic.
        Even if you refresh or close the browser. session data will still there.
    </h4>

    <hr />
    <h2 class="my-5 custom-title">Examples</h2>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Create Session</h4>
    <div class="rounded p-4 my-4 custom-div">
        <p class="mb-1">request.session['username'] = 'example_user'</p>
        <p class="mb-1">request.session['cart'] = ['item1', 'item2', 'item3']</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Update Session</h4>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-start mt-5">
        <h5 class="rounded my-4 p-3 custom-back">request.session['cart'].append('item4')</h5>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Adding a new item to the cart.</h4>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-start mt-5">
        <h5 class="rounded my-4 p-3 custom-back">request.session['username'] = 'new_username'</h5>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Changing the username.</h4>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Delete Session</h4>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-start mt-5">
        <h5 class="rounded my-4 p-3 custom-back">del request.session['cart']</h5>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Remove the cart from the session.</h4>
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-start mt-5">
        <h5 class="rounded my-4 p-3 custom-back">request.session.clear()</h5>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Clear all session data.</h4>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Get Session</h4>
    <div class="rounded p-4 my-4 custom-div">
        <p class="mb-1">username = request.session.get('username', 'default_username')</p>
        <p class="mb-1">cart_items = request.session.get('cart', [])</p>
    </div>
    <h4 class="mb-1 mt-4">Note: second parameter is default value. that means if username is null or not exist, username will equal 'default_username'.</h4>
</div>